cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as dimensionality reduction is a common technique used in machine learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word embeddings are used in information retrieval tasks. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as word embeddings are a fundamental component of many AI applications. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as word embeddings are often generated using neural network models.
